
'''Outsider Pull = the ability by an online community to consistently attract outsiders, so that the community dynamic remains open to the outside world.'''


=Comment by Ross Mayfield=

URL = http://many.corante.com/archives/2003/12/22/think_group.php

"the key to avoiding unhealthy levels of groupthink has to do with designing spaces that consistently exert pull upon outsiders (or social hackers or community straddlers), so as to keep the air fresh. As long as they feel welcomed, outsiders are able to inject an essential dose of criticism into a group's deliberations, which will help steer it out of groupthink potholes.
Seb goes on to say I think the blogosphere exhibits this kind of "outsider pull" much more than topic-focused forums"

